<br>
And just to add my support to Zellex, I completely agree with everything he said. Ninjalooters will have a bad time if their name is circulated among CoG leaders, because there are a lot of us. <br>
<br>
Harrassing language is not to be tolerated by a raid leader, and I've stated just such a thing before. One or two comments out of frustration is understandable. If you can't let it go or take it to tells after that, you will be banned at any raid I'm running, and I expect any CoG raid leader to follow their best judgement and do the same. <br>
<br>
Zellex, Pippi, and others who run CoG raids do so at great personal expense, often gaining no items, experience, or anything other than the fun of leading such a raid. Without their selfless efforts to run such raids, the CoG wouldn't exist, nor would it be successful. Take a moment to consider that, and be thankful for them, as I am. <br>
